{"title": "Reflections on Violence", "description": "Considered one of the more controversial books from the 20th century, Sorel's Reflections on Violence argues in favor of uprisings and strikes by the working class, which can be organized through the use of revolutionary myths. In the course of these direct actions any means is considered necessary and acceptable for the achievement of revolutionary politics. Upon successful overthrow of any established system, including democratic systems, the uprising working class can then setup syndicates as the only representative body of the people. (Summary by progressingamerica)", "duration": 42286, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "17875", "name": "Georges Sorel"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/reflectionsonviolence_2507_librivox/reflectionsonviolence_2507.jpg", "copyright_year": "1914", "genres": ["Political Science", "Modern"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "progressingamerica"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Christine Rottger"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Elsie Selwyn"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "A Note to the Third Edition, Introduction Parts I and II", "readers": [18692], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/reflectionsonviolence_2507_librivox/reflectionsonviolence_00_sorel_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2724}, {"section": 1, "title": "Introduction Parts III, IV, and V", "readers": [18692], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/reflectionsonviolence_2507_librivox/reflectionsonviolence_01_sorel_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2560}, {"section": 2, "title": "Introduction to the First Publication", "readers": [18946], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/reflectionsonviolence_2507_librivox/reflectionsonviolence_02_sorel_64kb.mp3", "duration": 832}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter I - Class War and Violence I", "readers": [20040], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/reflectionsonviolence_2507_